180 NTSTATUS
181 NtMapViewOfSection(
182  __in HANDLE SectionHandle,
183  __in HANDLE ProcessHandle,
184  __inout PVOID *BaseAddress,
185  __in ULONG_PTR ZeroBits,
186  __in SIZE_T CommitSize,
187  __inout_opt PLARGE_INTEGER SectionOffset,
188  __inout PSIZE_T ViewSize,
189  __in SECTION_INHERIT InheritDisposition,
190  __in ULONG AllocationType,
191  __in WIN32_PROTECTION_MASK Win32Protect
192  )
193 
194 /*++
195 
196 Routine Description:
197 
198  This function maps a view in the specified subject process to
199  the section object.
200 
201 Arguments:
202 
203  SectionHandle - Supplies an open handle to a section object.
204 
205  ProcessHandle - Supplies an open handle to a process object.
206 
207  BaseAddress - Supplies a pointer to a variable that will receive
208  the base address of the view. If the initial value
209  of this argument is not null, then the view will
210  be allocated starting at the specified virtual
211  address rounded down to the next 64kb address
212  boundary. If the initial value of this argument is
213  null, then the operating system will determine
214  where to allocate the view using the information
215  specified by the ZeroBits argument value and the
216  section allocation attributes (i.e. based and
217  tiled).
218 
219  ZeroBits - Supplies the number of high order address bits that
220  must be zero in the base address of the section
221  view. The value of this argument must be less than
222  or equal to the maximum number of zero bits and is only
223  used when memory management determines where to allocate
224  the view (i.e. when BaseAddress is null).
225 
226  If ZeroBits is zero, then no zero bit constraints are applied.
227 
228  If ZeroBits is greater than 0 and less than 32, then it is
229  the number of leading zero bits from bit 31. Bits 63:32 are
230  also required to be zero. This retains compatibility
231  with 32-bit systems.
232 
233  If ZeroBits is greater than 32, then it is considered as
234  a mask and the number of leading zeroes are counted out
235  in the mask. This then becomes the zero bits argument.
236 
237  CommitSize - Supplies the size of the initially committed region
238  of the view in bytes. This value is rounded up to
239  the next host page size boundary.
240 
241  SectionOffset - Supplies the offset from the beginning of the
242  section to the view in bytes. This value is
243  rounded down to the next host page size boundary.
244 
245  ViewSize - Supplies a pointer to a variable that will receive
246  the actual size in bytes of the view. If the value
247  of this argument is zero, then a view of the
248  section will be mapped starting at the specified
249  section offset and continuing to the end of the
250  section. Otherwise the initial value of this
251  argument specifies the size of the view in bytes
252  and is rounded up to the next host page size
253  boundary.
254 
255  InheritDisposition - Supplies a value that specifies how the
256  view is to be shared by a child process created
257  with a create process operation.
258 
259  InheritDisposition Values
260 
261  ViewShare - Inherit view and share a single copy
262  of the committed pages with a child process
263  using the current protection value.
264 
265  ViewUnmap - Do not map the view into a child process.
266 
267  AllocationType - Supplies the type of allocation.
268 
269  MEM_TOP_DOWN
270  MEM_DOS_LIM
271  MEM_LARGE_PAGES
272  MEM_RESERVE - for file mapped sections only.
273 
274  Win32Protect - Supplies the protection desired for the region of
275  initially committed pages.
276 
277  Win32Protect Values
278 
279  PAGE_NOACCESS - No access to the committed region
280  of pages is allowed. An attempt to read,
281  write, or execute the committed region
282  results in an access violation.
283 
284  PAGE_EXECUTE - Execute access to the committed
285  region of pages is allowed. An attempt to
286  read or write the committed region results in
287  an access violation.
288 
289  PAGE_READONLY - Read only and execute access to the
290  committed region of pages is allowed. An
291  attempt to write the committed region results
292  in an access violation.
293 
294  PAGE_READWRITE - Read, write, and execute access to
295  the region of committed pages is allowed. If
296  write access to the underlying section is
297  allowed, then a single copy of the pages are
298  shared. Otherwise the pages are shared read
299  only/copy on write.
300 
301 Return Value:
302 
303  Various NTSTATUS codes.
304 
305 --*/
306 
307 {
308  PSECTION Section;
309  PEPROCESS Process;
310  KPROCESSOR_MODE PreviousMode;
311  NTSTATUS Status;
312  PVOID CapturedBase;
313  SIZE_T CapturedViewSize;
314  LARGE_INTEGER CapturedOffset;
315  ULONGLONG HighestPhysicalAddressInPfnDatabase;
316  ACCESS_MASK DesiredSectionAccess;
317  ULONG ProtectMaskForAccess;
318  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
319  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
320 
321  PAGED_CODE();
322 
323  //
324  // Check the zero bits argument for correctness.
325  //
326 
327 #if defined (_WIN64)
328 
329  if (ZeroBits >= 32) {
330 
331  //
332  // ZeroBits is a mask instead of a count. Translate it to a count now.
333  //
334 
335  ZeroBits = 64 - RtlFindMostSignificantBit (ZeroBits) - 1;
336  }
337  else if (ZeroBits) {
338  ZeroBits += 32;
339  }
340 
341 #endif
342 
343  if (ZeroBits > MM_MAXIMUM_ZERO_BITS) {
344  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_4;
345  }
346 
347  //
348  // Check the inherit disposition flags.
349  //
350 
351  if ((InheritDisposition > ViewUnmap) ||
352  (InheritDisposition < ViewShare)) {
353  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_8;
354  }
355 
356  //
357  // Check the allocation type field.
358  //
359 
360 #ifdef i386
361 
362  //
363  // Only allow DOS_LIM support for i386. The MEM_DOS_LIM flag allows
364  // map views of data sections to be done on 4k boundaries rather
365  // than 64k boundaries.
366  //
367 
368  if ((AllocationType & ~(MEM_TOP_DOWN | MEM_LARGE_PAGES | MEM_DOS_LIM |
369  SEC_NO_CHANGE | MEM_RESERVE)) != 0) {
370  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_9;
371  }
372 #else
373  if ((AllocationType & ~(MEM_TOP_DOWN | MEM_LARGE_PAGES |
374  SEC_NO_CHANGE | MEM_RESERVE)) != 0) {
375  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_9;
376  }
377 
378 #endif //i386
379 
380  //
381  // Check the protection field.
382  //
383 
384  ProtectMaskForAccess = MiMakeProtectionMask (Win32Protect);
385  if (ProtectMaskForAccess == MM_INVALID_PROTECTION) {
386  return STATUS_INVALID_PAGE_PROTECTION;
387  }
388 
389  ProtectMaskForAccess = ProtectMaskForAccess & 0x7;
390 
391  DesiredSectionAccess = MmMakeSectionAccess[ProtectMaskForAccess];
392 
393  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
394  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcessByThread (CurrentThread);
395 
396  PreviousMode = KeGetPreviousModeByThread (&CurrentThread->Tcb);
397 
398  //
399  // Establish an exception handler, probe the specified addresses
400  // for write access and capture the initial values.
401  //
402 
403  try {
404 
405  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
406  ProbeForWritePointer (BaseAddress);
407  ProbeForWriteUlong_ptr (ViewSize);
408  }
409 
410  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (SectionOffset)) {
411  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
412  ProbeForWriteSmallStructure (SectionOffset,
413  sizeof(LARGE_INTEGER),
414  PROBE_ALIGNMENT (LARGE_INTEGER));
415  }
416  CapturedOffset = *SectionOffset;
417  }
418  else {
419  ZERO_LARGE (CapturedOffset);
420  }
421 
422  //
423  // Capture the base address.
424  //
425 
426  CapturedBase = *BaseAddress;
427 
428  //
429  // Capture the region size.
430  //
431 
432  CapturedViewSize = *ViewSize;
433 
434  } except (ExSystemExceptionFilter()) {
435 
436  //
437  // If an exception occurs during the probe or capture
438  // of the initial values, then handle the exception and
439  // return the exception code as the status value.
440  //
441 
442  return GetExceptionCode();
443  }
444 
445  //
446  // Make sure the specified starting and ending addresses are
447  // within the user part of the virtual address space.
448  //
449 
450  if (CapturedBase > MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS) {
451 
452  //
453  // Invalid base address.
454  //
455 
456  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_3;
457  }
458 
459  if (((ULONG_PTR)MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS - (ULONG_PTR)CapturedBase) <
460  CapturedViewSize) {
461 
462  //
463  // Invalid region size;
464  //
465 
466  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_3;
467 
468  }
469 
470  if (((ULONG_PTR)CapturedBase + CapturedViewSize) > ((ULONG_PTR)MM_USER_ADDRESS_RANGE_LIMIT >> ZeroBits)) {
471 
472  //
473  // Desired Base and zero_bits conflict.
474  //
475 
476  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_4;
477  }
478 
479  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (ProcessHandle,
480  PROCESS_VM_OPERATION,
481  PsProcessType,
482  PreviousMode,
483  (PVOID *)&Process,
484  NULL);
485  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
486  return Status;
487  }
488 
489  //
490  // Reference the section object, if a view is mapped to the section
491  // object, the object is not dereferenced as the virtual address
492  // descriptor contains a pointer to the section object.
493  //
494 
495  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle (SectionHandle,
496  DesiredSectionAccess,
497  MmSectionObjectType,
498  PreviousMode,
499  (PVOID *)&Section,
500  NULL);
501 
502  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
503  goto ErrorReturn1;
504  }
505 
506  //
507  // Check to see if this the section backs physical memory, if
508  // so DON'T align the offset on a 64K boundary, just a 4k boundary.
509  //
510 
511  if (Section->Segment->ControlArea->u.Flags.PhysicalMemory) {
512  CapturedOffset.LowPart = CapturedOffset.LowPart & ~(PAGE_SIZE - 1);
513 
514  //
515  // No usermode mappings past the end of the PFN database are allowed.
516  // Address wrap is checked in the common path.
517  //
518 
519  if (PreviousMode != KernelMode) {
520 
521  HighestPhysicalAddressInPfnDatabase = (ULONGLONG)MmHighestPhysicalPage << PAGE_SHIFT;
522 
523  if ((ULONGLONG)(CapturedOffset.QuadPart + CapturedViewSize) > HighestPhysicalAddressInPfnDatabase) {
524  Status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_6;
525  goto ErrorReturn;
526  }
527  }
528 
529  }
530  else {
531 
532  //
533  // Make sure alignments are correct for specified address
534  // and offset into the file.
535  //
536 
537  if ((AllocationType & MEM_DOS_LIM) == 0) {
538  if (((ULONG_PTR)CapturedBase & (X64K - 1)) != 0) {
539  Status = STATUS_MAPPED_ALIGNMENT;
540  goto ErrorReturn;
541  }
542 
543  if ((ARGUMENT_PRESENT (SectionOffset)) &&
544  ((CapturedOffset.LowPart & (X64K - 1)) != 0)) {
545  Status = STATUS_MAPPED_ALIGNMENT;
546  goto ErrorReturn;
547  }
548  }
549  }
550 
551  Status = MmMapViewOfSection ((PVOID)Section,
552  Process,
553  &CapturedBase,
554  ZeroBits,
555  CommitSize,
556  &CapturedOffset,
557  &CapturedViewSize,
558  InheritDisposition,
559  AllocationType,
560  Win32Protect);
561 
562  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status) ) {
563 
564  if ((Status == STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES) &&
565  (Section->Segment->ControlArea->u.Flags.Image) &&
566  (Process == CurrentProcess)) {
567 
568  DbgkMapViewOfSection (Section,
569  CapturedBase,
570  CapturedOffset.LowPart,
571  CapturedViewSize);
572  }
573  goto ErrorReturn;
574  }
575 
576  //
577  // Any time the current process maps an image file,
578  // a potential debug event occurs. DbgkMapViewOfSection
579  // handles these events.
580  //
581 
582  if ((Section->Segment->ControlArea->u.Flags.Image) &&
583  (Process == CurrentProcess)) {
584 
585  if (Status != STATUS_IMAGE_NOT_AT_BASE) {
586  DbgkMapViewOfSection (Section,
587  CapturedBase,
588  CapturedOffset.LowPart,
589  CapturedViewSize);
590  }
591  }
592 
593  //
594  // Establish an exception handler and write the size and base address.
595  //
596 
597  try {
598 
599  *ViewSize = CapturedViewSize;
600  *BaseAddress = CapturedBase;
601 
602  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT(SectionOffset)) {
603  *SectionOffset = CapturedOffset;
604  }
605 
606  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
607  NOTHING;
608  }
609 
610 ErrorReturn:
611  ObDereferenceObject (Section);
612 
613 ErrorReturn1:
614  ObDereferenceObject (Process);
615  return Status;
616 }

618 NTSTATUS
619 MmMapViewOfSection (
620  __in PVOID SectionToMap,
621  __in PEPROCESS Process,
622  __deref_inout_bcount(*CapturedViewSize) PVOID *CapturedBase,
623  __in ULONG_PTR ZeroBits,
624  __in SIZE_T CommitSize,
625  __inout PLARGE_INTEGER SectionOffset,
626  __inout PSIZE_T CapturedViewSize,
627  __in SECTION_INHERIT InheritDisposition,
628  __in ULONG AllocationType,
629  __in WIN32_PROTECTION_MASK Win32Protect
630  )
631 
632 /*++
633 
634 Routine Description:
635 
636  This function maps a view in the specified subject process to
637  the section object.
638 
639  This function is a kernel mode interface to allow LPC to map
640  a section given the section pointer to map.
641 
642  This routine assumes all arguments have been probed and captured.
643 
644  ********************************************************************
645  ********************************************************************
646  ********************************************************************
647 
648  NOTE:
649 
650  CapturedViewSize, SectionOffset, and CapturedBase must be
651  captured in non-paged system space (i.e., kernel stack).
652 
653  ********************************************************************
654  ********************************************************************
655  ********************************************************************
656 
657 Arguments:
658 
659  SectionToMap - Supplies a pointer to the section object.
660 
661  Process - Supplies a pointer to the process object.
662 
663  BaseAddress - Supplies a pointer to a variable that will receive
664  the base address of the view. If the initial value
665  of this argument is not NULL, then the view will
666  be allocated starting at the specified virtual
667  address rounded down to the next 64kb address
668  boundary. If the initial value of this argument is
669  NULL, then the operating system will determine
670  where to allocate the view using the information
671  specified by the ZeroBits argument value and the
672  section allocation attributes (i.e. based and
673  tiled).
674 
675  ZeroBits - Supplies the number of high order address bits that
676  must be zero in the base address of the section
677  view. The value of this argument must be less than
678  21 and is only used when the operating system
679  determines where to allocate the view (i.e. when
680  BaseAddress is NULL).
681 
682  CommitSize - Supplies the size of the initially committed region
683  of the view in bytes. This value is rounded up to
684  the next host page size boundary.
685 
686  SectionOffset - Supplies the offset from the beginning of the
687  section to the view in bytes. This value is
688  rounded down to the next host page size boundary.
689 
690  ViewSize - Supplies a pointer to a variable that will receive
691  the actual size in bytes of the view. If the value
692  of this argument is zero, then a view of the
693  section will be mapped starting at the specified
694  section offset and continuing to the end of the
695  section. Otherwise the initial value of this
696  argument specifies the size of the view in bytes
697  and is rounded up to the next host page size boundary.
698 
699  InheritDisposition - Supplies a value that specifies how the
700  view is to be shared by a child process created
701  with a create process operation.
702 
703  AllocationType - Supplies the type of allocation.
704 
705  Win32Protect - Supplies the protection desired for the region of
706  initially committed pages.
707 
708 Return Value:
709 
710  NTSTATUS.
711 
712 --*/
713 {
714  KAPC_STATE ApcState;
715  LOGICAL Attached;
716  PSECTION Section;
717  PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea;
718  ULONG ProtectionMask;
719  NTSTATUS status;
720  SIZE_T ImageCommitment;
721  LARGE_INTEGER TempViewSize;
722 
723  PAGED_CODE();
724 
725  Attached = FALSE;
726 
727  Section = (PSECTION)SectionToMap;
728 
729  if (Section->u.Flags.Image == 0) {
730 
731  //
732  // This is not an image section, make sure the section page
733  // protection is compatible with the specified page protection.
734  //
735 
736  if (!MiIsProtectionCompatible (Section->InitialPageProtection,
737  Win32Protect)) {
738  return STATUS_SECTION_PROTECTION;
739  }
740  }
741 
742  //
743  // Check to make sure the view size plus the offset is less
744  // than the size of the section.
745  //
746 
747  if ((ULONGLONG) (SectionOffset->QuadPart + *CapturedViewSize) <
748  (ULONGLONG)SectionOffset->QuadPart) {
749 
750  return STATUS_INVALID_VIEW_SIZE;
751  }
752 
753  if (((ULONGLONG) (SectionOffset->QuadPart + *CapturedViewSize) >
754  (ULONGLONG)Section->SizeOfSection.QuadPart) &&
755  ((AllocationType & MEM_RESERVE) == 0)) {
756 
757  return STATUS_INVALID_VIEW_SIZE;
758  }
759 
760  if (*CapturedViewSize == 0) {
761 
762  //
763  // Set the view size to be size of the section less the offset.
764  //
765 
766  TempViewSize.QuadPart = Section->SizeOfSection.QuadPart -
767  SectionOffset->QuadPart;
768 
769  *CapturedViewSize = (SIZE_T)TempViewSize.QuadPart;
770 
771  if (
772 
773 #if !defined(_WIN64)
774 
775  (TempViewSize.HighPart != 0) ||
776 
777 #endif
778 
779  (((ULONG_PTR)MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS - (ULONG_PTR)*CapturedBase) <
780  *CapturedViewSize)) {
781 
782  //
783  // Invalid region size;
784  //
785 
786  return STATUS_INVALID_VIEW_SIZE;
787  }
788  }
789 
790  //
791  // Check commit size.
792  //
793 
794  if ((CommitSize > *CapturedViewSize) &&
795  ((AllocationType & MEM_RESERVE) == 0)) {
796 
797  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_5;
798  }
799 
800  //
801  // Check to make sure the section is not smaller than the view size.
802  //
803 
804  if ((LONGLONG)*CapturedViewSize > Section->SizeOfSection.QuadPart) {
805  if ((AllocationType & MEM_RESERVE) == 0) {
806  return STATUS_INVALID_VIEW_SIZE;
807  }
808  }
809 
810  if (AllocationType & MEM_RESERVE) {
811  if (((Section->InitialPageProtection & PAGE_READWRITE) |
812  (Section->InitialPageProtection & PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE)) == 0) {
813 
814  return STATUS_SECTION_PROTECTION;
815  }
816  }
817 
818  if (Section->u.Flags.NoCache) {
819  Win32Protect |= PAGE_NOCACHE;
820  Win32Protect &= ~PAGE_WRITECOMBINE;
821  }
822 
823  if (Section->u.Flags.WriteCombined) {
824  Win32Protect |= PAGE_WRITECOMBINE;
825  Win32Protect &= ~PAGE_NOCACHE;
826  }
827 
828  //
829  // Check the protection field.
830  //
831 
832  ProtectionMask = MiMakeProtectionMask (Win32Protect);
833  if (ProtectionMask == MM_INVALID_PROTECTION) {
834  return STATUS_INVALID_PAGE_PROTECTION;
835  }
836 
837  ControlArea = Section->Segment->ControlArea;
838 
839  //
840  // If the specified process is not the current process, attach
841  // to the specified process.
842  //
843 
844  if (PsGetCurrentProcess() != Process) {
845  KeStackAttachProcess (&Process->Pcb, &ApcState);
846  Attached = TRUE;
847  }
848 
849  //
850  // Get the address creation mutex to block multiple threads
851  // creating or deleting address space at the same time.
852  //
853 
854  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
855 
856  //
857  // Make sure the address space was not deleted, if so, return an error.
858  //
859 
860  if (Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_VM_DELETED) {
861  status = STATUS_PROCESS_IS_TERMINATING;
862  goto ErrorReturn;
863  }
864 
865  //
866  // Map the view base on the type.
867  //
868 
869  if (ControlArea->u.Flags.PhysicalMemory) {
870 
871  status = MiMapViewOfPhysicalSection (ControlArea,
872  Process,
873  CapturedBase,
874  SectionOffset,
875  CapturedViewSize,
876  ProtectionMask,
877  ZeroBits,
878  AllocationType);
879  }
880  else if (ControlArea->u.Flags.Image) {
881  if (AllocationType & MEM_RESERVE) {
882  status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_9;
883  }
884  else if (Win32Protect & PAGE_WRITECOMBINE) {
885  status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_10;
886  }
887  else {
888 
889  ImageCommitment = Section->Segment->u1.ImageCommitment;
890 
891  status = MiMapViewOfImageSection (ControlArea,
892  Process,
893  CapturedBase,
894  SectionOffset,
895  CapturedViewSize,
896  Section,
897  InheritDisposition,
898  ZeroBits,
899  AllocationType,
900  ImageCommitment);
901  }
902  }
903  else {
904 
905  //
906  // Not an image section, therefore it is a data section.
907  //
908 
909  if (Win32Protect & PAGE_WRITECOMBINE) {
910  status = STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_10;
911  }
912  else {
913 
914  status = MiMapViewOfDataSection (ControlArea,
915  Process,
916  CapturedBase,
917  SectionOffset,
918  CapturedViewSize,
919  Section,
920  InheritDisposition,
921  ProtectionMask,
922  CommitSize,
923  ZeroBits,
924  AllocationType);
925  }
926  }
927 
928 ErrorReturn:
929  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
930 
931  if (Attached) {
932  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
933  }
934 
935  return status;
936 }
937 
938 VOID
939 MiInsertPhysicalViewAndRefControlArea (
940  IN PEPROCESS Process,
941  IN PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea,
942  IN PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW PhysicalView
943  )
944 
945 /*++
946 
947 Routine Description:
948 
949  This is a nonpaged helper routine to insert a physical view and reference
950  the control area accordingly.
951 
952 Arguments:
953 
954  Process - Supplies a pointer to the process.
955 
956  ControlArea - Supplies a pointer to the control area.
957 
958  PhysicalView - Supplies a pointer to the physical view.
959 
960 Return Value:
961 
962  None.
963 
964 Environment:
965 
966  Kernel Mode, address creation and working set mutex held.
967 
968 --*/
969 
970 {
971  KIRQL OldIrql;
972 
973  //
974  // Increment the count of the number of views for the
975  // section object. This requires the PFN lock to be held.
976  //
977 
978  ASSERT (PhysicalView->Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadDevicePhysicalMemory);
979 
980  ASSERT (Process->PhysicalVadRoot != NULL);
981 
982  MiInsertNode ((PMMADDRESS_NODE)PhysicalView, Process->PhysicalVadRoot);
983 
984  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
985 
986  ControlArea->NumberOfMappedViews += 1;
987  ControlArea->NumberOfUserReferences += 1;
988 
989  ASSERT (ControlArea->NumberOfSectionReferences != 0);
990 
991  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
992 }
993 
994 //
995 // Nonpaged wrapper.
996 //
997 LOGICAL
998 MiCheckCacheAttributes (
999  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
1000  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages,
1001  IN MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute
1002  )
1003 {
1004  KIRQL OldIrql;
1005  PMMPFN Pfn1;
1006  PFN_NUMBER BadFrameStart;
1007  PFN_NUMBER BadFrameEnd;
1008  LOGICAL AttemptedMapOfUnownedFrame;
1009 #if DBG
1010 #define BACKTRACE_LENGTH 8
1011  ULONG i;
1012  ULONG Hash;
1013  PVOID StackTrace [BACKTRACE_LENGTH];
1014  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
1015  PUNICODE_STRING BadDriverName;
1016 #endif
1017 
1018  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= APC_LEVEL);
1019 
1020  BadFrameStart = 0;
1021  BadFrameEnd = 0;
1022  AttemptedMapOfUnownedFrame = FALSE;
1023 
1024  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1025 
1026  do {
1027 
1028  if (MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
1029 
1030  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
1031 
1032  switch (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute) {
1033 
1034  case MiCached:
1035  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
1036  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1037  return FALSE;
1038  }
1039  break;
1040 
1041  case MiNonCached:
1042  if (CacheAttribute != MiNonCached) {
1043  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1044  return FALSE;
1045  }
1046  break;
1047 
1048  case MiWriteCombined:
1049  if (CacheAttribute != MiWriteCombined) {
1050  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1051  return FALSE;
1052  }
1053  break;
1054 
1055  case MiNotMapped:
1056  if (AttemptedMapOfUnownedFrame == FALSE) {
1057  BadFrameStart = PageFrameIndex;
1058  AttemptedMapOfUnownedFrame = TRUE;
1059  }
1060  BadFrameEnd = PageFrameIndex;
1061  break;
1062 
1063  default:
1064  ASSERT (FALSE);
1065  break;
1066  }
1067  }
1068  PageFrameIndex += 1;
1069  NumberOfPages -= 1;
1070  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
1071 
1072  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1073 
1074  if (AttemptedMapOfUnownedFrame == TRUE) {
1075 
1076 #if DBG
1077 
1078  BadDriverName = NULL;
1079 
1080  RtlZeroMemory (StackTrace, sizeof (StackTrace));
1081 
1082  RtlCaptureStackBackTrace (1, BACKTRACE_LENGTH, StackTrace, &Hash);
1083 
1084  for (i = 0; i < BACKTRACE_LENGTH; i += 1) {
1085 
1086  if (StackTrace[i] <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
1087  break;
1088  }
1089 
1090  DataTableEntry = MiLookupDataTableEntry (StackTrace[i], FALSE);
1091 
1092  if ((DataTableEntry != NULL) && ((PVOID)DataTableEntry != (PVOID)PsLoadedModuleList.Flink)) {
1093  //
1094  // Found the bad caller.
1095  //
1096 
1097  BadDriverName = &DataTableEntry->FullDllName;
1098  }
1099  }
1100 
1101  if (BadDriverName != NULL) {
1102  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
1103  "*******************************************************************************\n"
1104  "*\n"
1105  "* %wZ is mapping physical memory %p->%p\n"
1106  "* that it does not own. This can cause internal CPU corruption.\n"
1107  "*\n"
1108  "*******************************************************************************\n",
1109  BadDriverName,
1110  BadFrameStart << PAGE_SHIFT,
1111  (BadFrameEnd << PAGE_SHIFT) | (PAGE_SIZE - 1));
1112  }
1113  else {
1114  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
1115  "*******************************************************************************\n"
1116  "*\n"
1117  "* A driver is mapping physical memory %p->%p\n"
1118  "* that it does not own. This can cause internal CPU corruption.\n"
1119  "*\n"
1120  "*******************************************************************************\n",
1121  BadFrameStart << PAGE_SHIFT,
1122  (BadFrameEnd << PAGE_SHIFT) | (PAGE_SIZE - 1));
1123  }
1124 
1125 #else
1126  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
1127  "*******************************************************************************\n"
1128  "*\n"
1129  "* A driver is mapping physical memory %p->%p\n"
1130  "* that it does not own. This can cause internal CPU corruption.\n"
1131  "* A checked build will stop in the kernel debugger\n"
1132  "* so this problem can be fully debugged.\n"
1133  "*\n"
1134  "*******************************************************************************\n",
1135  BadFrameStart << PAGE_SHIFT,
1136  (BadFrameEnd << PAGE_SHIFT) | (PAGE_SIZE - 1));
1137 #endif
1138 
1139  if (MI_BP_BADMAPS()) {
1140  DbgBreakPoint ();
1141  }
1142  }
1143 
1144  return TRUE;
1145 }
1146 
1147 NTSTATUS
1148 MiMapViewOfPhysicalSection (
1149  IN PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea,
1150  IN PEPROCESS Process,
1151  IN PVOID *CapturedBase,
1152  IN PLARGE_INTEGER SectionOffset,
1153  IN PSIZE_T CapturedViewSize,
1154  IN ULONG ProtectionMask,
1155  IN ULONG_PTR ZeroBits,
1156  IN ULONG AllocationType
1157  )
1158 
1159 /*++
1160 
1161 Routine Description:
1162 
1163  This routine maps the specified physical section into the
1164  specified process's address space.
1165 
1166 Arguments:
1167 
1168  see MmMapViewOfSection above...
1169 
1170  ControlArea - Supplies the control area for the section.
1171 
1172  Process - Supplies the process pointer which is receiving the section.
1173 
1174  ProtectionMask - Supplies the initial page protection-mask.
1175 
1176 Return Value:
1177 
1178  Status of the map view operation.
1179 
1180 Environment:
1181 
1182  Kernel Mode, address creation mutex held.
1183 
1184 --*/
1185 
1186 {
1187  KIRQL OldIrql;
1188  PMMVAD_LONG Vad;
1189  PETHREAD Thread;
1190  CSHORT IoMapping;
1191  PVOID StartingAddress;
1192  PVOID EndingAddress;
1193  PVOID HighestUserAddress;
1194  PMMPTE PointerPde;
1195  PMMPTE PointerPte;
1196  PMMPTE LastPte;
1197  PMMPTE LastPde;
1198  MMPTE TempPte;
1199  PMMPFN Pfn2;
1200  SIZE_T PhysicalViewSize;
1201  ULONG_PTR Alignment;
1202  PVOID UsedPageTableHandle;
1203  PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW PhysicalView;
1204  NTSTATUS Status;
1205  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
1206  PFN_NUMBER StartingPageFrameIndex;
1207  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
1208  MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType;
1209  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
1210  LOGICAL TryLargePages;
1211 
1212  //
1213  // Physical memory section.
1214  //
1215 
1216  if (AllocationType & (MEM_RESERVE | MEM_LARGE_PAGES)) {
1217  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_9;
1218  }
1219 
1220  if ((MI_IS_GUARD (ProtectionMask)) ||
1221  (ProtectionMask == MM_NOACCESS)) {
1222 
1223  //
1224  // These cannot be represented with valid PTEs so reject these
1225  // requests. Note copy on write doesn't make any sense for these
1226  // either, but those can be safely rejected if/when the application
1227  // really does try to write to the mapping.
1228  //
1229 
1230  return STATUS_INVALID_PAGE_PROTECTION;
1231  }
1232 
1233  TryLargePages = FALSE;
1234 
1235  if (((SectionOffset->QuadPart & (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE - 1)) == 0) &&
1236 #ifdef _X86_
1237  (KeFeatureBits & KF_LARGE_PAGE) &&
1238 #endif
1239  (ZeroBits == 0) &&
1240  ((*CapturedViewSize & (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE - 1)) == 0)) {
1241  }
1242 
1243  Alignment = X64K;
1244 
1245  if (*CapturedBase == NULL) {
1246 
1247  //
1248  // Attempt to locate address space starting on a 64k boundary.
1249  //
1250 
1251 #if !defined (_MI_MORE_THAN_4GB_)
1252  ASSERT (SectionOffset->HighPart == 0);
1253 #endif
1254 
1255  if (TryLargePages == TRUE) {
1256 
1257  PhysicalViewSize = *CapturedViewSize;
1258 
1259  //
1260  // Check whether the registry indicates that all applications
1261  // should be given virtual address ranges from the highest
1262  // address downwards in order to test 3GB-aware apps on 32-bit
1263  // machines and 64-bit apps on NT64.
1264  //
1265 
1266  if ((AllocationType & MEM_TOP_DOWN) || (Process->VmTopDown == 1)) {
1267 
1268  HighestUserAddress = MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS;
1269 
1270  Status = MiFindEmptyAddressRangeDown (&Process->VadRoot,
1271  PhysicalViewSize,
1272  HighestUserAddress,
1273  MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE,
1274  &StartingAddress);
1275  }
1276  else {
1277 
1278  Status = MiFindEmptyAddressRange (PhysicalViewSize,
1279  MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE,
1280  (ULONG)ZeroBits,
1281  &StartingAddress);
1282  }
1283 
1284  if (NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1285 
1286  EndingAddress = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)StartingAddress +
1287  PhysicalViewSize - 1L);
1288  goto GotRange;
1289  }
1290  }
1291 
1292  TryLargePages = FALSE;
1293 
1294  PhysicalViewSize = *CapturedViewSize +
1295  (SectionOffset->LowPart & (X64K - 1));
1296 
1297  //
1298  // Check whether the registry indicates that all applications
1299  // should be given virtual address ranges from the highest
1300  // address downwards in order to test 3GB-aware apps on 32-bit
1301  // machines and 64-bit apps on NT64.
1302  //
1303 
1304  if ((AllocationType & MEM_TOP_DOWN) || (Process->VmTopDown == 1)) {
1305 
1306  if (ZeroBits != 0) {
1307  HighestUserAddress = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)MM_USER_ADDRESS_RANGE_LIMIT >> ZeroBits);
1308  if (HighestUserAddress > MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS) {
1309  HighestUserAddress = MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS;
1310  }
1311  }
1312  else {
1313  HighestUserAddress = MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS;
1314  }
1315 
1316  Status = MiFindEmptyAddressRangeDown (&Process->VadRoot,
1317  PhysicalViewSize,
1318  HighestUserAddress,
1319  Alignment,
1320  &StartingAddress);
1321  }
1322  else {
1323 
1324  Status = MiFindEmptyAddressRange (PhysicalViewSize,
1325  Alignment,
1326  (ULONG)ZeroBits,
1327  &StartingAddress);
1328  }
1329 
1330  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1331  return Status;
1332  }
1333 
1334  EndingAddress = (PVOID)(((ULONG_PTR)StartingAddress +
1335  PhysicalViewSize - 1L) | (PAGE_SIZE - 1L));
1336  StartingAddress = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)StartingAddress +
1337  (SectionOffset->LowPart & (X64K - 1)));
1338 
1339  if (ZeroBits > 0) {
1340  if (EndingAddress > (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)MM_USER_ADDRESS_RANGE_LIMIT >> ZeroBits)) {
1341  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1342  }
1343  }
1344  }
1345  else {
1346 
1347  //
1348  // Check to make sure the specified base address to ending address
1349  // is currently unused.
1350  //
1351 
1352  StartingAddress = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)MI_64K_ALIGN(*CapturedBase) +
1353  (SectionOffset->LowPart & (X64K - 1)));
1354  EndingAddress = (PVOID)(((ULONG_PTR)StartingAddress +
1355  *CapturedViewSize - 1L) | (PAGE_SIZE - 1L));
1356 
1357  if (MiCheckForConflictingVadExistence (Process, StartingAddress, EndingAddress) == TRUE) {
1358  return STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES;
1359  }
1360 
1361  if ((ULONG_PTR)*CapturedBase & (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE - 1)) {
1362  TryLargePages = FALSE;
1363  }
1364  }
1365 
1366 GotRange:
1367 
1368  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartingAddress);
1369  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress (EndingAddress);
1370 
1371  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (StartingAddress);
1372 
1373  //
1374  // If a noncachable mapping is requested, none of the physical pages in the
1375  // range can reside in a large cached page. Otherwise we would be
1376  // creating an incoherent overlapping TB entry as the same physical
1377  // page would be mapped by 2 different TB entries with different
1378  // cache attributes.
1379  //
1380 
1381  StartingPageFrameIndex = (PFN_NUMBER) (SectionOffset->QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
1382 
1383  //
1384  // Build the PTE.
1385  //
1386 
1387  MI_MAKE_VALID_USER_PTE (TempPte,
1388  StartingPageFrameIndex,
1389  ProtectionMask,
1390  PointerPte);
1391 
1392  if (TempPte.u.Hard.Write) {
1393  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
1394  }
1395 
1396  MI_ADD_EXECUTE_TO_VALID_PTE_IF_PAE (TempPte);
1397 
1398  //
1399  // See if the mapping is to I/O space. If so, the cache attribute may
1400  // need to be updated to work around hardware platform problems.
1401  //
1402 
1403  IoMapping = 1;
1404 
1405  if (MI_IS_PFN (StartingPageFrameIndex)) {
1406  IoMapping = 0;
1407  }
1408 
1409  //
1410  // For non I/O space mappings, we already have the correct attributes
1411  // in the PTE. But we still need to compute the CacheAttribute variable
1412  // so we'll know if the cache needs to be swept, etc.
1413  //
1414 
1415  CacheType = MmCached;
1416 
1417  if (MI_IS_WRITECOMBINE (ProtectionMask)) {
1418  CacheType = MmWriteCombined;
1419  }
1420  else if (MI_IS_NOCACHE (ProtectionMask)) {
1421  CacheType = MmNonCached;
1422  }
1423 
1424  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, IoMapping);
1425 
1426  NumberOfPages = LastPte - PointerPte + 1;
1427 
1428  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
1429 
1430  if (CacheAttribute == MiWriteCombined) {
1431  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
1432  }
1433  else if (CacheAttribute == MiNonCached) {
1434  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
1435  }
1436 
1437  PageFrameIndex = StartingPageFrameIndex;
1438 
1439  while (PageFrameIndex < StartingPageFrameIndex + NumberOfPages) {
1440  if (MI_PAGE_FRAME_INDEX_MUST_BE_CACHED (PageFrameIndex)) {
1441  MiNonCachedCollisions += 1;
1442  return STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES;
1443  }
1444  PageFrameIndex += 1;
1445  }
1446  }
1447 
1448  //
1449  // An unoccupied address range has been found, build the virtual
1450  // address descriptor to describe this range.
1451  //
1452 
1453  //
1454  // The working set mutex synchronizes the allocation of the
1455  // EPROCESS PhysicalVadRoot. This table root is not deleted until
1456  // the process exits.
1457  //
1458 
1459  if ((Process->PhysicalVadRoot == NULL) &&
1460  (MiCreatePhysicalVadRoot (Process, FALSE) == NULL)) {
1461 
1462  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1463  }
1464 
1465  //
1466  // Attempt to allocate the pool and charge quota during the Vad insertion.
1467  //
1468 
1469  PhysicalView = (PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW)ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
1470  sizeof(MI_PHYSICAL_VIEW),
1471  MI_PHYSICAL_VIEW_KEY);
1472  if (PhysicalView == NULL) {
1473  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1474  }
1475 
1476  Vad = (PMMVAD_LONG)ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
1477  sizeof(MMVAD_LONG),
1478  'ldaV');
1479  if (Vad == NULL) {
1480  ExFreePool (PhysicalView);
1481  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1482  }
1483 
1484  RtlZeroMemory (Vad, sizeof(MMVAD_LONG));
1485  Vad->StartingVpn = MI_VA_TO_VPN (StartingAddress);
1486  Vad->EndingVpn = MI_VA_TO_VPN (EndingAddress);
1487  Vad->ControlArea = ControlArea;
1488  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.Inherit = MM_VIEW_UNMAP;
1489  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.LongVad = 1;
1490  Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType = VadDevicePhysicalMemory;
1491  Vad->u.VadFlags.Protection = ProtectionMask;
1492 
1493  PhysicalView->Vad = (PMMVAD) Vad;
1494  PhysicalView->StartingVpn = Vad->StartingVpn;
1495  PhysicalView->EndingVpn = Vad->EndingVpn;
1496  PhysicalView->VadType = VadDevicePhysicalMemory;
1497 
1498  //
1499  // Set the last contiguous PTE field in the Vad to the page frame
1500  // number of the starting physical page.
1501  //
1502 
1503  Vad->LastContiguousPte = (PMMPTE) StartingPageFrameIndex;
1504 
1505  Vad->FirstPrototypePte = (PMMPTE) StartingPageFrameIndex;
1506 
1507  ASSERT (Vad->FirstPrototypePte <= Vad->LastContiguousPte);
1508 
1509  //
1510  // Ensure no page frame cache attributes conflict.
1511  //
1512 
1513  if (MiCheckCacheAttributes (StartingPageFrameIndex, NumberOfPages, CacheAttribute) == FALSE) {
1514  Status = STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES;
1515  goto Failure1;
1516  }
1517 
1518  //
1519  // Insert the VAD. This could fail due to quota charges.
1520  //
1521 
1522  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
1523 
1524  Status = MiInsertVadCharges ((PMMVAD) Vad, Process);
1525 
1526  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
1527 
1528 Failure1:
1529  ExFreePool (PhysicalView);
1530 
1531  //
1532  // The pool allocation succeeded but the quota charge failed,
1533  // deallocate the pool and return an error.
1534  //
1535 
1536  ExFreePool (Vad);
1537  return Status;
1538  }
1539 
1540  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
1541 
1542  MiInsertVad ((PMMVAD) Vad, Process);
1543 
1544  //
1545  // Build the PTEs in the address space.
1546  //
1547 
1548  MI_PREPARE_FOR_NONCACHED (CacheAttribute);
1549 
1550  if (TryLargePages == TRUE) {
1551 
1552 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
1553 
1554  //
1555  // Temporarily make the VAD protection no access. This allows
1556  // us to safely release the working set mutex while trying to
1557  // find contiguous memory to fill the large page range.
1558  // If another thread tries to access the large page VA range
1559  // before we find (and insert) a contiguous chunk, the thread
1560  // will get an AV.
1561  //
1562 
1563  Vad->u.VadFlags.Protection = MM_NOACCESS;
1564 
1565  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
1566 
1567  //
1568  // Lock down the page directory page(s) as these entries are not
1569  // going to be paged.
1570  //
1571 
1572  Status = MiAllocateLargePages (StartingAddress,
1573  EndingAddress,
1574  ProtectionMask,
1575  TRUE);
1576 
1577  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {

4159 NTSTATUS
4160 MiCheckPurgeAndUpMapCount (
4161  IN PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea,
4162  IN LOGICAL FailIfSystemViews
4163  )
4164 
4165 /*++
4166 
4167 Routine Description:
4168 
4169  This routine synchronizes with any on going purge operations
4170  on the same segment (identified via the control area). If
4171  another purge operation is occurring, the function blocks until
4172  it is completed.
4173 
4174  When this function returns the MappedView and the NumberOfUserReferences
4175  count for the control area will be incremented thereby referencing
4176  the control area.
4177 
4178 Arguments:
4179 
4180  ControlArea - Supplies the control area for the segment to be purged.
4181 
4182  FailIfSystemViews - Supplies TRUE if the request should fail when there
4183  are active kernel mappings. When the image is mapped
4184  in system or session space as a driver, copy on write
4185  does not work so user processes are not allowed to
4186  map the image.
4187 
4188 Return Value:
4189 
4190  STATUS_SUCCESS if the synchronization was successful.
4191  NTSTATUS if the synchronization did not occur due to low resources, etc.
4192 
4193 Environment:
4194 
4195  Kernel Mode.
4196 
4197 --*/
4198 
4199 {
4200  NTSTATUS Status;
4201  KIRQL OldIrql;
4202  PEVENT_COUNTER PurgedEvent;
4203  PEVENT_COUNTER WaitEvent;
4204  PKTHREAD CurrentThread;
4205 
4206  PurgedEvent = NULL;
4207 
4208  if (FailIfSystemViews == TRUE) {
4209  ASSERT (ControlArea->u.Flags.Image != 0);
4210  }
4211 
4212  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4213 
4214  while (ControlArea->u.Flags.BeingPurged != 0) {
4215 
4216  //
4217  // A purge operation is in progress.
4218  //
4219 
4220  if (PurgedEvent == NULL) {
4221 
4222  //
4223  // Release the locks and allocate pool for the event.
4224  //
4225 
4226  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4227  PurgedEvent = MiGetEventCounter ();
4228  if (PurgedEvent == NULL) {
4229  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4230  }
4231 
4232  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4233  continue;
4234  }
4235 
4236  if (ControlArea->WaitingForDeletion == NULL) {
4237  ControlArea->WaitingForDeletion = PurgedEvent;
4238  WaitEvent = PurgedEvent;
4239  PurgedEvent = NULL;
4240  }
4241  else {
4242  WaitEvent = ControlArea->WaitingForDeletion;
4243 
4244  //
4245  // No interlock is needed for the RefCount increment as
4246  // no thread can be decrementing it since it is still
4247  // pointed to by the control area.
4248  //
4249 
4250  WaitEvent->RefCount += 1;
4251  }
4252 
4253  //
4254  // Release the PFN lock and wait for the event.
4255  //
4256 
4257  CurrentThread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
4258  KeEnterCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
4259  UNLOCK_PFN_AND_THEN_WAIT(OldIrql);
4260 
4261  KeWaitForSingleObject (&WaitEvent->Event,
4262  WrVirtualMemory,
4263  KernelMode,
4264  FALSE,
4265  (PLARGE_INTEGER)NULL);
4266 
4267  //
4268  // Before this event can be set, the control area WaitingForDeletion
4269  // field must be cleared (and may be reinitialized to something else),
4270  // but cannot be reset to our local event. This allows us to
4271  // dereference the event count lock free.
4272  //
4273 
4274  ASSERT (WaitEvent != ControlArea->WaitingForDeletion);
4275 
4276  MiFreeEventCounter (WaitEvent);
4277 
4278  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4279  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
4280  }
4281 
4282  if ((FailIfSystemViews == TRUE) &&
4283  (ControlArea->u.Flags.ImageMappedInSystemSpace) &&
4284  (KeGetPreviousMode() != KernelMode)) {
4285 
4286  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4287  Status = STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES;
4288  }
4289  else {
4290 
4291  //
4292  // Indicate another file is mapped for the segment.
4293  //
4294 
4295  ControlArea->NumberOfMappedViews += 1;
4296  ControlArea->NumberOfUserReferences += 1;
4297  ASSERT (ControlArea->NumberOfSectionReferences != 0);
4298 
4299  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4300  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4301  }
4302 
4303  if (PurgedEvent != NULL) {
4304  MiFreeEventCounter (PurgedEvent);
4305  }
4306 
4307  return Status;
4308 }

4672

4875 #else

4880

4882

4885

4888  //

5286  }
5287 #endif
5288 
5289 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)

5328

5330  // No page table page exists, get a page and map it in.
5331  //
5332 
5333  TempPte = ValidKernelPde;

5336 
5337  if (FirstSystemPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5338 
5339  if ((MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) &&

5361 #else

5364  FirstPde,
5365  MmSystemPageDirectory[i]);

5372  //
5373

5382  }

5390  PointerPxe = MiGetPdeAddress (FirstPde);
5391  }
5392  }
5393 #endif
5394  } while (FirstPde <= LastPde);

5533 PVOID
5534 MiInsertInSystemSpace (
5535  IN PMMSESSION Session,
5536  IN ULONG SizeIn64k,
5537  IN PCONTROL_AREA ControlArea
5538  )
5539 
5540 /*++
5541 
5542 Routine Description:
5543 
5544  This routine creates a view in system space for the specified control
5545  area (file mapping).
5546 
5547 Arguments:
5548 
5549  SizeIn64k - Supplies the size of the view to be created.
5550 
5551  ControlArea - Supplies a pointer to the control area for this view.
5552 
5553 Return Value:
5554 
5555  Base address where the view was mapped, NULL if the view could not be
5556  mapped.
5557 
5558 Environment:
5559 
5560  Kernel Mode.
5561 
5562 --*/
5563 
5564 {
5565 
5566  PVOID Base;
5567  ULONG_PTR Entry;
5568  ULONG Hash;
5569  ULONG i;
5570  ULONG AllocSize;
5571  PMMVIEW OldTable;
5572  ULONG StartBit;
5573  ULONG NewHashSize;
5574  POOL_TYPE PoolType;
5575 
5576  PAGED_CODE();
5577 
5578  ASSERT (SizeIn64k < X64K);
5579 
5580  //
5581  // CODE IS ALREADY LOCKED BY CALLER.
5582  //
5583 
5584  LOCK_SYSTEM_VIEW_SPACE (Session);
5585 
5586  if (Session->SystemSpaceHashEntries + 8 > Session->SystemSpaceHashSize) {
5587 
5588  //
5589  // Less than 8 free slots, reallocate and rehash.
5590  //
5591 
5592  NewHashSize = Session->SystemSpaceHashSize << 1;
5593 
5594  AllocSize = sizeof(MMVIEW) * NewHashSize;
5595 
5596  OldTable = Session->SystemSpaceViewTable;
5597 
5598  //
5599  // The SystemSpaceViewTable for system (not session) space is only
5600  // allocated from nonpaged pool so it can be safely torn down during
5601  // clean shutdowns. Otherwise it could be allocated from paged pool
5602  // just like the session SystemSpaceViewTable.
5603  //
5604 
5605  if (Session == &MmSession) {
5606  PoolType = NonPagedPool;
5607  }
5608  else {
5609  PoolType = PagedPool;
5610  }
5611 
5612  Session->SystemSpaceViewTable = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PoolType,
5613  AllocSize,
5614  ' mM');
5615 
5616  if (Session->SystemSpaceViewTable == NULL) {
5617  Session->SystemSpaceViewTable = OldTable;
5618  }
5619  else {
5620  RtlZeroMemory (Session->SystemSpaceViewTable, AllocSize);
5621 
5622  Session->SystemSpaceHashSize = NewHashSize;
5623  Session->SystemSpaceHashKey = Session->SystemSpaceHashSize - 1;
5624 
5625  for (i = 0; i < (Session->SystemSpaceHashSize / 2); i += 1) {
5626  if (OldTable[i].Entry != 0) {
5627  Hash = (ULONG) ((OldTable[i].Entry >> 16) % Session->SystemSpaceHashKey);
5628 
5629  while (Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash].Entry != 0) {
5630  Hash += 1;
5631  if (Hash >= Session->SystemSpaceHashSize) {
5632  Hash = 0;
5633  }
5634  }
5635  Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash] = OldTable[i];
5636  }
5637  }
5638  ExFreePool (OldTable);
5639  }
5640  }
5641 
5642  if (Session->SystemSpaceHashEntries == Session->SystemSpaceHashSize) {
5643 
5644  //
5645  // There are no free hash slots to place a new entry into even
5646  // though there may still be unused virtual address space.
5647  //
5648 
5649  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_VIEW_SPACE (Session);
5650  return NULL;
5651  }
5652 
5653  StartBit = RtlFindClearBitsAndSet (Session->SystemSpaceBitMap,
5654  SizeIn64k,
5655  0);
5656 
5657  if (StartBit == NO_BITS_FOUND) {
5658  Session->BitmapFailures += 1;
5659  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_VIEW_SPACE (Session);
5660  return NULL;
5661  }
5662 
5663  Base = (PVOID)((PCHAR)Session->SystemSpaceViewStart + ((ULONG_PTR)StartBit * X64K));
5664 
5665  Entry = (ULONG_PTR) MI_64K_ALIGN(Base) + SizeIn64k;
5666 
5667  Hash = (ULONG) ((Entry >> 16) % Session->SystemSpaceHashKey);
5668 
5669  while (Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash].Entry != 0) {
5670  Hash += 1;
5671  if (Hash >= Session->SystemSpaceHashSize) {
5672  Hash = 0;
5673  }
5674  }
5675 
5676  Session->SystemSpaceHashEntries += 1;
5677 
5678  Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash].Entry = Entry;
5679  Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash].ControlArea = ControlArea;
5680 
5681  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_VIEW_SPACE (Session);
5682  return Base;
5683 }

5686 ULONG
5687 MiRemoveFromSystemSpace (
5688  IN PMMSESSION Session,
5689  IN PVOID Base,
5690  OUT PCONTROL_AREA *ControlArea
5691  )
5692 
5693 /*++
5694 
5695 Routine Description:
5696 
5697  This routine looks up the specified view in the system space hash
5698  table and unmaps the view from system space and the table.
5699 
5700 Arguments:
5701 
5702  Session - Supplies the session data structure for this view.
5703 
5704  Base - Supplies the base address for the view. If this address is
5705  NOT found in the hash table, the system bugchecks.
5706 
5707  ControlArea - Returns the control area corresponding to the base
5708  address.
5709 
5710 Return Value:
5711 
5712  Size of the view divided by 64k.
5713 
5714 Environment:
5715 
5716  Kernel Mode, system view hash table locked.
5717 
5718 --*/
5719 
5720 {
5721  ULONG_PTR Base16;
5722  ULONG Hash;
5723  ULONG Size;
5724  ULONG count;
5725 
5726  PAGED_CODE();
5727 
5728  count = 0;
5729 
5730  Base16 = (ULONG_PTR)Base >> 16;
5731  Hash = (ULONG)(Base16 % Session->SystemSpaceHashKey);
5732 
5733  while ((Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash].Entry >> 16) != Base16) {
5734  Hash += 1;
5735  if (Hash >= Session->SystemSpaceHashSize) {
5736  Hash = 0;
5737  count += 1;
5738  if (count == 2) {
5739  KeBugCheckEx (DRIVER_UNMAPPING_INVALID_VIEW,
5740  (ULONG_PTR)Base,
5741  1,
5742  0,
5743  0);
5744  }
5745  }
5746  }
5747 
5748  Session->SystemSpaceHashEntries -= 1;
5749  Size = (ULONG) (Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash].Entry & 0xFFFF);
5750  Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash].Entry = 0;
5751  *ControlArea = Session->SystemSpaceViewTable[Hash].ControlArea;
5752  return Size;
5753 }

5756 LOGICAL
5757 MiInitializeSystemSpaceMap (
5758  PVOID InputSession OPTIONAL
5759  )
5760 
5761 /*++
5762 
5763 Routine Description:
5764 
5765  This routine initializes the tables for mapping views into system space.
5766  Views are kept in a multiple of 64k bytes in a growable hashed table.
5767 
5768 Arguments:
5769 
5770  InputSession - Supplies NULL if this is the initial system session
5771  (non-Hydra), a valid session pointer (the pointer must
5772  be in global space, not session space) for Hydra session
5773  initialization.
5774 
5775 Return Value:
5776 
5777  TRUE on success, FALSE on failure.
5778 
5779 Environment:
5780 
5781  Kernel Mode, initialization.
5782 
5783 --*/
5784 
5785 {
5786  SIZE_T AllocSize;
5787  SIZE_T Size;
5788  PCHAR ViewStart;
5789  PMMSESSION Session;
5790  POOL_TYPE PoolType;
5791 
5792  if (ARGUMENT_PRESENT (InputSession)) {
5793  Session = (PMMSESSION)InputSession;
5794  ViewStart = (PCHAR) MiSessionViewStart;
5795  Size = MmSessionViewSize;
5796  }
5797  else {
5798  Session = &MmSession;
5799  ViewStart = (PCHAR)MiSystemViewStart;
5800  Size = MmSystemViewSize;
5801  }
5802 
5803  //
5804  // We are passed a system global address for the address of the session.
5805  // Save a global pointer to the mutex below because multiple sessions will
5806  // generally give us a session-space (not a global space) pointer to the
5807  // MMSESSION in subsequent calls. We need the global pointer for the mutex
5808  // field for the kernel primitives to work properly.
5809  //
5810 
5811  Session->SystemSpaceViewLockPointer = &Session->SystemSpaceViewLock;
5812  KeInitializeGuardedMutex (Session->SystemSpaceViewLockPointer);
5813 
5814  //
5815  // If the kernel image has not been biased to allow for 3gb of user space,
5816  // then the system space view starts at the defined place. Otherwise, it
5817  // starts 16mb above the kernel image.
5818  //
5819 
5820  Session->SystemSpaceViewStart = ViewStart;
5821 
5822  MiCreateBitMap (&Session->SystemSpaceBitMap, Size / X64K, NonPagedPool);
5823  if (Session->SystemSpaceBitMap == NULL) {
5824  MM_BUMP_SESSION_FAILURES (MM_SESSION_FAILURE_NO_NONPAGED_POOL);
5825  return FALSE;
5826  }
5827 
5828  RtlClearAllBits (Session->SystemSpaceBitMap);
5829 
5830  //
5831  // Build the view table.
5832  //
5833 
5834  Session->SystemSpaceHashSize = 31;
5835  Session->SystemSpaceHashKey = Session->SystemSpaceHashSize - 1;
5836  Session->SystemSpaceHashEntries = 0;
5837 
5838  AllocSize = sizeof(MMVIEW) * Session->SystemSpaceHashSize;
5839  ASSERT (AllocSize < PAGE_SIZE);
5840 
5841  //
5842  // The SystemSpaceViewTable for system (not session) space is only
5843  // allocated from nonpaged pool so it can be safely torn down during
5844  // clean shutdowns. Otherwise it could be allocated from paged pool
5845  // just like the session SystemSpaceViewTable.
5846  //
5847 
5848  if (Session == &MmSession) {
5849  PoolType = NonPagedPool;
5850  }
5851  else {
5852  PoolType = PagedPool;
5853  }
5854 
5855  Session->SystemSpaceViewTable = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (PoolType,
5856  AllocSize,
5857  ' mM');
5858 
5859  if (Session->SystemSpaceViewTable == NULL) {
5860  MM_BUMP_SESSION_FAILURES (MM_SESSION_FAILURE_NO_SESSION_PAGED_POOL);
5861  MiRemoveBitMap (&Session->SystemSpaceBitMap);
5862  return FALSE;
5863  }
5864 
5865  RtlZeroMemory (Session->SystemSpaceViewTable, AllocSize);
5866 
5867  return TRUE;
5868 }

5970 
5971 HANDLE
5972 MiSecureVirtualMemory (
5973  IN PVOID Address,
5974  IN SIZE_T Size,
5975  IN ULONG ProbeMode,
5976  IN LOGICAL AddressSpaceMutexHeld
5977  )
5978 
5979 /*++
5980 
5981 Routine Description:
5982 
5983  This routine probes the requested address range and protects
5984  the specified address range from having its protection made
5985  more restricted and being deleted.
5986 
5987  MmUnsecureVirtualMemory is used to allow the range to return
5988  to a normal state.
5989 
5990 Arguments:
5991 
5992  Address - Supplies the base address to probe and secure.
5993 
5994  Size - Supplies the size of the range to secure.
5995 
5996  ProbeMode - Supplies one of PAGE_READONLY or PAGE_READWRITE.
5997 
5998  AddressSpaceMutexHeld - Supplies TRUE if the mutex is already held, FALSE
5999  if not.
6000 
6001 Return Value:
6002 
6003  Returns a handle to be used to unsecure the range.
6004  If the range could not be locked because of protection
6005  problems or noncommitted memory, the value (HANDLE)0
6006  is returned.
6007 
6008 Environment:
6009 
6010  Kernel Mode.
6011 
6012 --*/
6013 
6014 {
6015  PETHREAD Thread;
6016  ULONG_PTR EndAddress;
6017  PVOID StartAddress;
6018  CHAR Temp;
6019  ULONG Probe;
6020  HANDLE Handle;
6021  PMMVAD Vad;
6022  PMMVAD VadParent;
6023  PMMVAD_LONG NewVad;
6024  PMMSECURE_ENTRY Secure;
6025  PEPROCESS Process;
6026  PMMPTE PointerPxe;
6027  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
6028  PMMPTE PointerPde;
6029  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6030  PMMPTE LastPte;
6031  ULONG Waited;
6032 #if defined(_WIN64)
6033  ULONG_PTR PageSize;
6034 #else
6035  #define PageSize PAGE_SIZE
6036 #endif
6037 
6038  PAGED_CODE();
6039 
6040  if ((ULONG_PTR)Address + Size > (ULONG_PTR)MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS || (ULONG_PTR)Address + Size <= (ULONG_PTR)Address) {
6041  return NULL;
6042  }
6043 
6044  Handle = NULL;
6045 
6046  Probe = (ProbeMode == PAGE_READONLY);
6047 
6048  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
6049  Process = PsGetCurrentProcessByThread (Thread);
6050 
6051 #if defined(_WIN64)
6052  if (Process->Wow64Process != NULL) {
6053  PageSize = PAGE_SIZE_X86NT;
6054  }
6055  else {
6056  PageSize = PAGE_SIZE;
6057  }
6058 #endif
6059 
6060  StartAddress = Address;
6061 
6062  if (AddressSpaceMutexHeld == FALSE) {
6063  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
6064  }
6065 
6066  //
6067  // Check for a private committed VAD first instead of probing to avoid all
6068  // the page faults and zeroing. If we find one, then we run the PTEs
6069  // instead.
6070  //
6071 
6072  if (Size >= 64 * 1024) {
6073  EndAddress = (ULONG_PTR)StartAddress + Size - 1;
6074  Vad = MiLocateAddress (StartAddress);
6075 
6076  if (Vad == NULL) {
6077  goto Return1;
6078  }
6079 
6080  if ((Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadAwe) ||
6081  (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadLargePages)) {
6082  goto Return1;
6083  }
6084

6626 VOID

6628  IN HANDLE SecureHandle,
6629  IN LOGICAL AddressSpaceMutexHeld
6630  )
6631 
6632 /*++
6633 
6634 Routine Description:
6635 
6636  This routine unsecures memory previously secured via a call to
6637  MmSecureVirtualMemory.
6638 
6639 Arguments:
6640 
6641  SecureHandle - Supplies the handle returned in MmSecureVirtualMemory.
6642 
6643  AddressSpaceMutexHeld - Supplies TRUE if the mutex is already held, FALSE
6644  if not.
6645 
6646 Return Value:
6647 
6648  None.
6649 
6650 Environment:
6651 
6652  Kernel Mode.
6653 
6654 --*/
6655 
6656 {
6657  PMMSECURE_ENTRY Secure;
6658  PEPROCESS Process;
6659  PMMVAD_LONG Vad;
6660 
6661  PAGED_CODE();
6662 
6663  Secure = (PMMSECURE_ENTRY)SecureHandle;
6664  Process = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
6665 
6666  if (AddressSpaceMutexHeld == FALSE) {
6667  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
6668  }
6669 
6670  //
6671  // Make sure the address space was not deleted (ie, the thread that
6672  // secured the virtual memory was attached). If the process has exited,
6673  // then our VAD (or MMSECURE) pointer has already been freed so just
6674  // return.
6675  //
6676 
6677  if (Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_VM_DELETED) {
6678 
6679  if (AddressSpaceMutexHeld == FALSE) {
6680  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
6681  }
6682 
6683  return;
6684  }
6685 
6686  if ((ULONG_PTR)Secure & 0x1) {
6687  Secure = (PMMSECURE_ENTRY) ((ULONG_PTR)Secure & ~0x1);
6688  Vad = CONTAINING_RECORD (Secure,
6689  MMVAD_LONG,
6690  u2.LongFlags2);
6691  }
6692  else {
6693  Vad = (PMMVAD_LONG) MiLocateAddress ((PVOID)Secure->StartVpn);
6694  }
6695 
6696  ASSERT (Vad);
6697  ASSERT (Vad->u.VadFlags.NoChange == 1);
6698  ASSERT (Vad->u2.VadFlags2.LongVad == 1);
6699 
6700  if (Vad->u2.VadFlags2.OneSecured) {
6701  ASSERT (Secure == (PMMSECURE_ENTRY)&Vad->u2.LongFlags2);
6702  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.OneSecured = 0;
6703  ASSERT (Vad->u2.VadFlags2.MultipleSecured == 0);
6704  if (Vad->u2.VadFlags2.SecNoChange == 0) {
6705 
6706  //
6707  // No more secure entries in this list, remove the state.
6708  //
6709 
6710  Vad->u.VadFlags.NoChange = 0;
6711  }
6712  if (AddressSpaceMutexHeld == FALSE) {
6713  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
6714  }
6715  }
6716  else {
6717  ASSERT (Vad->u2.VadFlags2.MultipleSecured == 1);
6718 
6719  if (Secure == (PMMSECURE_ENTRY)&Vad->u2.LongFlags2) {
6720 
6721  //
6722  // This was a single block that got converted into a list.
6723  // Reset the entry.
6724  //
6725 
6726  Secure = CONTAINING_RECORD (Vad->u3.List.Flink,
6727  MMSECURE_ENTRY,
6728  List);
6729  }
6730  RemoveEntryList (&Secure->List);
6731  if (IsListEmpty (&Vad->u3.List)) {
6732 
6733  //
6734  // No more secure entries, reset the state.
6735  //
6736 
6737  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.MultipleSecured = 0;
6738 
6739  if ((Vad->u2.VadFlags2.SecNoChange == 0) &&
6740  (Vad->u.VadFlags.PrivateMemory == 0)) {
6741 
6742  //
6743  // No more secure entries in this list, remove the state
6744  // if and only if this VAD is not private. If this VAD
6745  // is private, removing the state NoChange flag indicates
6746  // that this is a short VAD which it no longer is.
6747  //
6748 
6749  Vad->u.VadFlags.NoChange = 0;
6750  }
6751  }
6752  if (AddressSpaceMutexHeld == FALSE) {
6753  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
6754  }
6755  ExFreePool (Secure);
6756  }
6757 
6758  return;
6759 }
